Well, today I flew this plane.
The first complaint: we need a cute flight log book. Black is too boring, and pink isn't really pink—it's salmon red.
I've always wanted to fly.
Today my dream came true... I actually flew a plane today. I'm still not fully coming to terms with it.
FlightAware data.
I planned to try again on Saturday. The weather doesn't look good now, but today is Monday.
The challenges in this area seem to be starting to show. Due to the FAA's stance on certain medications, I may have difficulty obtaining a medical certificate.
This is not impossible, but it will take a lot of time and require a lot of extra work.
Although this is a bit discouraging, it's just another problem to solve, and it does seem "possible" at the moment. It just requires a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges I'm facing next:
FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you're taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't get your medical certificate.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
If I ever get the chance to customize the tail number of my plane, it has to be some variant of N1337_, where _ represents any available letter character.
Of course, the sun will still rise even when I'm not around, haha. What a letdown.
I need to fly again. But this terrible weather is just not cooperating.
Welcome to the world of general aviation! 😜
Based on the ads YouTube thinks I should see, the videos it recommends to me, and the comments, I feel airlines tend to be conservative in their tracking.
If the weather allows, I'll fly again on Saturday.
